  "title": "PostgreSQL DBA (Junior & Senior)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><p>We are looking for a Junior PostgreSQL DBA to support the daily operation and maintenance of database systems. The role focuses on assisting senior DBAs in database monitoring, maintenance, backup, security, and high-availability environments, while developing hands-on experience in PostgreSQL administration.<br /></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Assist in supporting and maintaining database environments, including monitoring systems, backup systems, log systems, and automation tools under guidance.</li><li>Support daily PostgreSQL and MySQL database monitoring, operation, and basic troubleshooting.</li><li>Assist in database maintenance tasks such as routine checks, backups, and performance monitoring.</li><li>Support database security hardening activities to ensure data integrity and backup availability.</li><li>Participate in database cutovers and operational activities, including master-slave switchovers, data synchronization, and data migration, under supervision.</li><li>Assist in database performance testing and optimization tasks in production or test environments.</li><li>Support the setup and maintenance of database clusters and disaster recovery environments.</li><li>Document operational procedures and follow established database operation standards.</li><li>Provide basic technical support to team members and escalate issues when required.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s Degree, Diploma, or Professional Qualification in Computer Science, Information Technology, or equivalent.</li></ul><ul><li>2–3 years of experience in database administration, PostgreSQL, or related IT roles).</li></ul><ul><li>Basic knowledge of PostgreSQL database concepts and operations.</li></ul><ul><li>Familiarity with SQL statements and basic performance analysis.</li></ul><ul><li>Basic understanding of database monitoring and backup concepts.</li></ul><ul><li>Willingness to learn database automation, high availability, and disaster recovery solutions.</li></ul><ul><li>Good problem-solving skills and ability to work under guidance.</li></ul><ul><li>Team player with a positive learning attitude.</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred Skills (Advantageous)</strong></p><ul><li>Exposure to MySQL databases.</li><li>Exposure to database monitoring or automation systems.</li><li>Basic understanding of high-availability or cluster database environments.</li><li>Awareness of database security best practices.</li><li>Experience supporting websites or application databases is a plus.</li></ul><p><strong>Company Benefits</strong></p><ul><li>Attractive rewards for long-term service staff.</li><li>Friendly working environment with flexible working hours, and staff birthday celebrations.</li><li>Medical insurance coverage.</li></ul>",
